# Backend Patterns

## API Design
- Use RESTful conventions
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes
- Use DTOs for request/response, never expose entities
- Version your APIs

## Database
- Use Repository pattern with Unit of Work
- Implement Specification pattern for complex queries
- Use EF Core migrations
- Optimize with .AsNoTracking() for read-only queries

## Error Handling
- Use Result pattern for business logic errors
- Use ProblemDetails for API errors
- Never expose internal error details to clients
